<TITLE> BNP to chalk out anti-government campaign </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 16 (bdnews24.com) - Opposition leader Khaleda Zia will be meeting her party's top leaders on Sunday evening to chalk out its anti-government campaign programmes as well as to take a decision on who should be the party's candidate in the Chittagong City Corporation election. The meeting of the standing committee will take place at Khaleda's Gulshan office and will start at 8 pm. BNP standing committee member Nazrul Islam Khan told bdnews24.com that the meeting will discuss the programmes for a strong anti-government campaign which will be publicly declared from the party's grand rally in Dhaka set to be held on May 19. He said that Khaleda Zia will declare the programmes as the last speaker taking place at Paltan. On Thursday the leaders of the BNP in Chittagong decided to take part in the CCC election, stating that the election would form part of their anti-government campaign. No candidate has yet been chosen by the BNP. According to the election commission schedule the CCC polls will be held on June 17 with the last date for submission of nomination papers being May 20. EC will then scrutinise the nomination papers on May 22 and 23  with June 1 as the last date for withdrawal of nomination. bd
